## Documentation Framework

1. Purpose

   - Support development process
   - Document patterns and decisions
   - Guide without constraining
   - Enable knowledge sharing

2. Organization

   - .workspace/docs/ref/: External references and standards
   - .workspace/docs/temp/: Work in progress documentation
   - .workspace/docs/arch/: Architecture and design docs
   - Project docs live in `.workspace/docs/` (assistant-agnostic)
   - Assistant-specific rule docs remain in their own directories (e.g., `.cursor/`, `.claude/`)

3. Best Practices
   - Centralize shared project docs in `.workspace/docs/`
   - Keep assistant-specific guidance in their respective directories (`.cursor/`, `.claude/`)
   - Use clear cross-references between `.workspace/docs/` and assistant-specific rules
   - Maintain docs regularly and keep them assistant-agnostic by default
